here's coverage for Authentication, but why not for Redirect? Maybe the active report indicates that the file wasn't included. I might need to use Groovy's static dispatch like the existing tests, but there could be an issue with GroovySystem initialization in native images. Still, JVM coverage via the agent should ideally invoke everything.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Investigating MethodHandle issues**\\n\\nI’m considering whether the class$ method might not exist in the dependency jar during tests, even though it appears in the build effective. It seems that MethodHandle should invoke, but perhaps the report is checking dynamic access during the native image run instead of JVM. Using MethodHandles.privateLookupIn requires reflection metadata, which may not be available in native. The uncovered call sites indicate an issue, especially since the generic Map<String,Object> passed to the Groovy constructor might affect compilation. I also need to check if invokeExact failed due to WrongMethodType.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering Class.forName behavior**\\n\\nI’m reflecting on whether Class.forName(\\\"io.restassured.internal.RedirectSpecificationImpl\\\") might be affected by the constant class already being loaded. It still calls Class.forName, which should be caught by the dynamic access instrumentation. This raises some questions: Is the instrumentation properly tracking the access patterns, and why might it not be capturing this instance? I really need to dig deeper into both the loading process and the instrumentation to understand what's happening here.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_LK7ZvsOW3yl9IOF7eUun3ukM|fc_0c402cbe3c1f8a5a016a00a909f2f081a1bdec363a2d94b397", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find tests/src/io.rest-assured/rest-assured/5.5.0/build/reports -type f | grep -i RedirectSpecificationImplTest || true && grep -R \"RedirectSpecificationImplTest\" -n tests/src/io.rest-assured/rest-assured/5.5.0/